
[1]curtate

   CURTATE, a. [L., to shorten.] The curtate distance, in astronomy, is
   the distance of a planet from the sun to that point, where a
   perpendicular let fall from the planet meets with the ecliptic. Or the
   interval between the sun or earth, and that point where a
   perpendicular, let fall from the planet, meets the ecliptic.
